BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:padimai-onchain-artist-residency-oops-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260815
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260816
SUMMARY:Deadline: Padimai: OOPS Onchain Artist Residency 2026
DESCRIPTION:OOPS (Origin Of Primary Source) is the first edition of Padimai
  Art and Tech Studio's Onchain Artist Residency\, a three-month remote res
 idency inviting art practitioners to critically and creatively engage with
  NFTs as artistic registers and as systems of knowledge\, documentation\, 
 and access. Five practitioners are selected. SUPPORT: SGD 15\,000 honorari
 um per artist\, plus SGD 5\,000 per artist for documentation. The residenc
 y is remote\, with community engagement designed through online meetings\;
  at the end\, participants deliver three NFTs developed during the residen
 cy to Padimai. ELIGIBILITY: individual creative practitioners working at t
 he intersection of art\, technology\, and blockchain\; open internationall
 y. RESIDENCY: 20 September to 20 December 2026. DEADLINE: 15 August 2026. 
 Apply via the residency page.\n\nOrganisation: Padimai Art and Tech Studio
 \nLocation: Remote residency (Padimai is based in Singapore)\; open intern
 ationally.\nAward: SGD 15\,000 honorarium per artist plus an additional SG
 D 5\,000 per artist for documentation (audio\, video\, photography). Five 
 practitioners selected. No application fee.\nDuration: 3 months (20 Septem
 ber to 20 December 2026)\n\nMore: https://padimai.net/onchain-artist-resid
 ency/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://padimai.net/onchain-artist-residency/?utm_source=artificialnouv
 eaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Remote residency (Padimai is based in Singapore)\; open internatio
 nally.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:gifct-memberships-programs-internship-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260801
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260802
SUMMARY:Deadline: GIFCT: Internship\, Memberships & Programs
DESCRIPTION:GIFCT is hiring a part-time intern to support its Memberships a
 nd Programs team. Work spans three areas: open-source research and early h
 uman rights assessments on companies applying to the Membership Advisory P
 rogram\, reviewing them against GIFCT's Membership Criteria\; assisting th
 e annual member review process and mapping companies that could benefit fr
 om GIFCT tools\; and helping update the Definitions and Legislation Projec
 t with new case studies and resources. Generalist exposure to an organisat
 ion working at the intersection of technology\, trust and safety\, and cou
 nterterrorism policy\, including drafting communications\, records\, event
  logistics and reporting. Strong written and organisational skills require
 d\; interest in tech policy\, trust and safety\, human rights or internati
 onal security is a plus. Reports to Dr. Nagham El Karhili. Apply by emaili
 ng a resume plus answers to three short questions (in lieu of a cover lett
 er) to jobs@gifct.org with 'M&P Internship' in the subject line. NOTE: thi
 s is a paid internship\, not a grant or fellowship. Deadline 1 August 2026
 .\n\nOrganisation: Global Internet Forum to Counter Terrorism (GIFCT)\nLoc
 ation: Remote (preference for US Eastern timezone)\nAward: Paid role: $25/
 hour\, part-time at a maximum of 24 hours per week (3 days a week). No app
 lication fee.\nDuration: Mid-August to mid-December 2026\n\nMore: https://
 gifct.org/opportunities/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=
 referral#internship--memberships---programs
URL:https://gifct.org/opportunities/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&
 utm_medium=referral#internship--memberships---programs
LOCATION:Remote (preference for US Eastern timezone)
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:rand-cast-fellowship-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260722T221148Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260801
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260802
SUMMARY:Deadline: Center on AI\, Security\, and Technology (CAST) Fellowshi
 p
DESCRIPTION:RAND's Center on AI\, Security\, and Technology (CAST) runs a r
 olling fellowship for researchers working on AI security and technology po
 licy\, with mentorship from RAND policy experts. Fellows can be based in W
 ashington DC\, San Francisco or Pittsburgh\, work remotely within the Unit
 ed States\, or be based in the United Kingdom. Terms are flexible: engagem
 ents typically start at six months and can be extended up to three years\,
  full-time or part-time. US fellows receive an annual stipend ranging from
  USD 40\,000 to 200\,000 for full-time work depending on experience\, plus
  a monthly payment that can be put toward health and dental insurance\; UK
  fellows are compensated based on experience. The programme spans career s
 tages from undergraduate through mid-career. ELIGIBILITY: applicants must 
 be based in the US or UK\; US applicants need to be eligible for a governm
 ent security clearance\, and UK applicants must have a current and ongoing
  right to work in the UK. Current RAND staff are not eligible. ROLLING DEA
 DLINE: applications are submitted through an online form and reviewed quar
 terly\, with published cutoffs of 1 February\, 1 May\, 1 August and 1 Nove
 mber\, each answered by the first of the following month. The date recorde
 d here is the next cutoff (1 August 2026)\; the call does not close after 
 it. RAND notes that if one of its listed staff openings matches your inter
 est you should apply to that instead\, and suggests not applying to the fe
 llowship if you have submitted another CAST application within the last si
 x months.\n\nOrganisation: RAND Corporation\, Center on AI\, Security\, an
 d Technology (CAST)\nLocation: Washington DC\, San Francisco or Pittsburgh
 \, USA\, or remote within the United States\; fellows may also be based in
  the United Kingdom\nAward: US fellows: annual stipend from USD 40\,000 to
  200\,000 for full-time fellows depending on experience\, plus a monthly p
 ayment usable for health and dental insurance. UK fellows: compensation ba
 sed on experience. No application fee.\nDuration: Typically starts at 6 mo
 nths\, extendable up to 3 years\; full-time or part-time\n\nMore: https://
 www.rand.org/global-and-emerging-risks/centers/ai-security-and-technology/
 fellows.html?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.rand.org/global-and-emerging-risks/centers/ai-security-and-
 technology/fellows.html?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=r
 eferral
LOCATION:Washington DC\, San Francisco or Pittsburgh\, USA\, or remote with
 in the United States\; fellows may also be based in the United Kingdom
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
